::sy701_1_1 Security control categories::Which of the following best describes a detective control?{
=Monitoring and alerting on suspicious activity
~Blocking unauthorized access before it occurs
~Physically preventing entry to a data center
~Replacing a failed control with a compensating control
}

::sy701_1_2 CIA triad::Which principle ensures that data has not been altered without authorization?{
=Integrity
~Confidentiality
~Availability
~Non-repudiation
}

::sy701_1_3 Change management::Why is a documented backout plan important during change management?{
=It enables safe rollback if a change introduces security or operational issues
~It eliminates the need for maintenance windows
~It replaces the need for version control
~It guarantees zero downtime for every change
}

::sy701_1_4 Cryptographic hashing::What is the primary purpose of salting passwords before hashing?{
=To defend against rainbow table attacks
~To encrypt passwords for reversible storage
~To replace the need for key escrow
~To sign messages with a private key
}

::sy701_2_1 Threat actors::Which motivation is most commonly associated with organized crime threat actors?{
=Financial gain
~Political hacktivism
~Nation-state espionage only
~Accidental insider mistakes
}

::sy701_2_2 Attack vectors::Phishing delivered via SMS is commonly referred to as what?{
=Smishing
~Vishing
~Typosquatting
~Watering hole
}

::sy701_2_3 Vulnerabilities::A buffer overflow is best categorized as which type of vulnerability?{
=Application
~Physical
~Policy
~Environmental
}

::sy701_2_4 Malicious activity indicators::Impossible travel alerts are most closely related to detecting what?{
=Account compromise or credential misuse
~Expired TLS certificates
~Misconfigured DNS records
~Hardware end-of-life
}

::sy701_2_5 Mitigation::Applying least privilege primarily reduces what risk?{
=Unauthorized access to resources beyond job requirements
~Network latency on encrypted links
~Certificate revocation delays
~Backup storage costs
}

::sy701_3_1 Architecture models::Which model shifts infrastructure management to a cloud provider while the customer configures security controls for workloads?{
=Shared responsibility in cloud computing
~Air-gapped on-premises only
~Fully decentralized peer-to-peer
~Single-tenant mainframe only
}

::sy701_3_2 Secure infrastructure::An inline IPS placed on a network path is primarily used to what?{
=Detect and block malicious traffic in real time
~Archive logs for long-term retention only
~Replace the need for encryption
~Generate self-signed certificates
}

::sy701_3_3 Data protection::Tokenization is primarily used to protect data by doing what?{
=Replacing sensitive values with non-sensitive substitutes
~Compressing files for faster backup
~Deleting data at end of life
~Publishing data to an open ledger
}

::sy701_3_4 Resilience::A warm site typically provides what compared to a hot site?{
=Partially configured infrastructure with longer recovery time
~No data replication capability
~Only offsite tape backups with no network
~Immediate failover with zero RTO
}

::sy701_4_1 Secure baselines::Establishing a secure baseline for servers most directly supports which goal?{
=Consistent hardening and reduced configuration drift
~Eliminating the need for patching
~Removing all administrative accounts
~Disabling all logging to save storage
}

::sy701_4_2 Asset management::Sanitization during asset disposal primarily prevents what?{
=Data remanence on decommissioned media
~Certificate expiration
~DNS cache poisoning
~Social engineering
}

::sy701_4_3 Vulnerability management::A false positive in vulnerability scanning means what?{
=A reported vulnerability is not actually present
~A real vulnerability was missed by the scanner
~A patch was applied successfully
~A risk was accepted permanently
}

::sy701_4_4 Monitoring::A SIEM is primarily used to what?{
=Aggregate and correlate security events for analysis and alerting
~Encrypt data at rest on endpoints
~Replace identity and access management
~Issue digital certificates
}

::sy701_4_5 Network security::A web application firewall (WAF) is designed to protect what?{
=Web applications at Layer 7
~Layer 2 switching loops
~Physical access to a server room
~Email SPF records only
}

::sy701_4_6 IAM::Multifactor authentication requires how many distinct factor categories?{
=Two or more
~Exactly one
~Only biometric factors
~Only knowledge factors
}

::sy701_4_7 Automation::Orchestration in security operations most directly improves what?{
=Coordinated response across multiple tools and processes
~Manual ticket duplication
~Removal of audit trails
~Permanent exception handling
}

::sy701_4_8 Incident response::Which incident response phase focuses on limiting damage and preventing spread?{
=Containment
~Preparation
~Lessons learned
~Detection only
}

::sy701_4_9 Investigation::Maintaining chain of custody is critical during what activity?{
=Digital forensics evidence handling
~Password policy updates
~Vendor contract renewal
~Security awareness training
}

::sy701_5_1 Governance::An Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) is an example of what governance element?{
=Policy
~Procedure only
~Technical control
~Penetration test report
}

::sy701_5_2 Risk management::Annualized Loss Expectancy (ALE) combines which concepts?{
=Single Loss Expectancy and Annualized Rate of Occurrence
~RTO and RPO only
~CVSS and CVE only
~SLA and MOU only
}

::sy701_5_3 Third-party risk::A right-to-audit clause in a vendor contract enables what?{
=The organization to verify vendor security controls
~Unlimited data sharing with suppliers
~Automatic exemption from compliance
~Removal of SLA penalties
}

::sy701_5_4 Compliance::Data sovereignty requirements primarily concern what?{
=Where data is stored and processed geographically
~Which antivirus vendor is selected
~How often passwords expire
~Which IDS signatures are enabled
}

::sy701_5_5 Audits::An external regulatory examination is best classified as what?{
=External assessment
~Self-assessment only
~Tabletop exercise
~Bug bounty program
}

::sy701_5_6 Security awareness::Simulated phishing campaigns are primarily used to what?{
=Measure and improve user recognition of social engineering
~Replace technical email filtering
~Eliminate the need for DMARC
~Archive firewall logs
}
